1, "span": {"begin": 2377, "end": 2383}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3554"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-1R1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9960582852363586, "span": {"begin": 2448, "end": 2454}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3557"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IL-1R antagonist", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9020825624465942, "span": {"begin": 2468, "end": 2484}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7852"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CXCR4", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9824124574661255, "span": {"begin": 2530, "end": 2535}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3553"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IL-1&beta", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9945148229598999, "span": {"begin": 2547, "end": 2556}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mRNA", "obj": "RNA", "prob": 0.8358891010284424, "span": {"begin": 2566, "end": 2570}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6387"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SDF-1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9916150569915771, "span": {"begin": 2610, "end": 2615}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "murine lymphocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8088715672492981, "span": {"begin": 2689, "end": 2707}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10090"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "murine", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.8935974836349487, "span": {"begin": 2689, "end": 2695}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human monocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8492221236228943, "span": {"begin": 2712, "end": 2727}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9012713432312012, "span": {"begin": 2712, "end": 2717}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human or murine neutrophils", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8804680109024048, "span": {"begin": 2751, "end": 2778}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9881179928779602, "span": {"begin": 2751, "end": 2756}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10090"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "murine", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9727096557617188, "span": {"begin": 2760, "end": 2766}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6387"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SDF-1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9955710768699646, "span": {"begin": 2780, "end": 2785}}], "text": "It was shown that a number of chemokines destabilize the rolling of lymphocytes on L-selectin ligands, suggesting that chemokines are capable of regulating the rolling process (Grabovsky et al., 2002).  Jorgensen and colleagues showed that exposure of mice to FliCind strain S. Typhimurium triggered a significant neutrophil influx in the spleen of wild-type mice, but not Il1b&minus;/&minus;Il18&minus;/&minus; mice (Jorgensen et al., 2016).  The expression of chemokines CCL2, CCL7, and CCL12 was reduced dramatically in MyD88-/- mice (Lee et al., 2009).  Miyamoto and colleagues showed that exposure of cells to IL-1&beta;, TNF-&alpha;, and IFN-&gamma; resulted in the induction of RANTES mRNA and protein (Ortiz et al., 1996; Miyamoto et al., 2000). The levels of RANTES production by the fibroblasts in the presence of IL-1&beta; or TNF-&alpha; were significantly elevated compared with those in the absence of these factors (Yamada et al., 2001).  In the mouse, IFN-&gamma; administration induces high levels of IP-10 expression in liver and kidneys, with lower levels in spleen (Narumi et al., 1992).  CAPE inhibitor of NF-kB blocked partially IL-1&beta; induced expression of chemokines MIP-1a and MIP-1b (Guo et al., 2003).  CCR2 and CCR5 receptors on the CD8 T cells are enriched in the inflamed human liver, and CCR1 is important in the regulation of hepatic inflammation in murine models (Shields et al., 1999; Boisvert et al., 2003). &nbsp;  Intradermal injection of RANTES induces a potent T-lymphocyte and eosinophils recruitment (Fahy et al., 2001; Beck et al., 1997). &nbsp;Intradermal administration of MIP-1a resulted in accumulation of monocytes, lymphocytes, eosinophils and recruitment of neutrophils (Lee et al., 2000).  Direct IL-1&alpha; exposure to the gut resulted in increased numbers of CD3+ cells in the fetal sheep ileum when compared with control animals on the first day after the exposure. The number of white blood cells, monocytes, and neutrophils was increased in cord blood after 6 days of IL-1&alpha; exposure to the lung and chorioamnion/skin. The number of lymphocytes on the day 6 was increased for the lung. Compared with controls, gut mRNA levels of TNF-&alpha; and IL-1 was significantly increased at 6 days after IL-1&alpha; exposure to the GI tract (Nikiforou et al., 2016).  IL-1 &beta; induced up-regulation of CXCR4 in certain cancer cells, but in order to do so necessary is that these cells have IL-1R1. Presence of IL-1R antagonist significantly inhibited the up-regulation of CXCR4 induced by IL-1&beta; at both mRNA and protein level (Sun et al., 2015).  SDF-1 is an efficacious chemoattractant and showed a similar dose response for murine lymphocytes and human monocytes, but was not active on human or murine neutrophils. SDF-1 is a highly effective transendothelial chemoattractant (Bleul et al., 1996).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:50:50 +0000 2026"}